Diagnosis. Pectoral fin present; dorsal-fin origin slightly anterior to pectoral-fin base, predorsal length 10.7– 13.1 % TL; anus anterior, below tip of pectoral fin, preanal length 15.9–18.9 % TL; trunk very short, 2.8–5.5 % TL; two intermaxillary teeth; 4 compound teeth on vomer; single row of 9–11 large compound teeth on lower jaw; head pores: IO 4 , SO 3 ; M 6 ; POP 0; AD 1 , F 0, ST 0; lateral-line pores: predorsal 3–6 , prepectoral 6–9 , preanal 8–12 , total 57–75 , the last at posterior two-thirds of total length; MVF 8-14 - 124 , total vertebrae 119–128 ( 119–130 in
Robins & Robins, 1989
).
